# JavaScript / TypeScript Standards

- Prefer small, single-purpose functions; extract helpers instead of long inline logic.
- Use dependency injection for external deps (HTTP, DB, queues) when testing or swapping impls.
- Use table-driven / parameterized tests: one `describe` or `it.each` per behavior, cases in an array.
- No comments for obvious logic; short comments only for non-obvious or spec-critical behavior.
- Preserve existing patterns (CommonJS vs ESM, async style, naming) when adding code.
- Prefer `const`; avoid mutable globals. Use TypeScript types for public APIs.

## Table-style tests (Jest / Vitest)

```js
describe('parsePrefs', () => {
  it.each([
    ['{"email":true}', { email: true }, false],
    ['{', null, true],
  ])('input %s -> wantErr %s', (input, want, wantErr) => {
    if (wantErr) {
      expect(() => parsePrefs(input)).toThrow();
    } else {
      expect(parsePrefs(input)).toEqual(want);
    }
  });
});
```

## Error handling

- Prefer throwing or returning Result-like values; do not swallow errors.
- For retries/backoff, use explicit intervals (e.g. from spec: 1 min, 5 min, 15 min).
